ion is comparable\nto that of the manual picks but the increased number of picks per event for the\nML pickers, especially PhaseNet, yields smaller hypocentral errors. The number\nof associated events per hour increases for seismically quiet times of the day,\nand the smallest magnitude events are detected throughout these periods, which\nwe interpret to be indicative of true event associations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 May 2022 12:31:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-25"}
